metadata.name: Unskilled Labour
metadata.description:
In India, a "cross road" will have a number of people sitting in the corner early in the morning. They are standing out for a job.

The means of survival for daily labourers are unstable.

India is a place where every morning a daily labour needs to seek his work for the day.

It can involve assisting to clear a passage for a road expansion or lifting a huge cement bag at a building site. They are a developing country's true developers.
